  "text": "In multiple experimental colitis models, mice do not develop colitis under germfree conditions. We next asked whether microbiota could affect colitis induction via regulation of T cell spontaneous proliferation. As reported previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , the total number of splenic CD4 + and CD8 + T cells in germfree mice are only 80% of that of conventional SPF mice, indicating a mild lymphopenic condition. To further investigate the role of intestinal microbiota in T cell spontaneous proliferation, CFSE-labeled CBir1 Tg CD4 + T cells or OT II CD4 + T cells were transferred into RAG / mice housed in conventional SPF conditions or in germfree conditions. 10 d later, T cell they only underwent homeostatic proliferation but not spontaneous proliferation in the recipients reconstituted with CBL-pulsed IL-6 / BMDCs (Fig. 4 D) , demonstrating that DC IL-6 production plays a crucial role in the CD4 + T cell spontaneous proliferation driven by the microbiota.",
